00:45:30.220 --> 00:45:31.620
is that this is not sustainable.

00:45:31.620 --> 00:45:36.311
Eventually, they burn out in discouragement,
or they get caught and they get fired. More

00:45:36.311 --> 00:45:41.790
hopeful are the people we call "system changers."
These are people working within the practice

00:45:41.790 --> 00:45:48.770
of law, the practice of medicine, who see
that they are not training their new doctors

00:45:48.770 --> 00:45:53.790
and lawyers well and are trying to create
systems for training, medical training, that

00:45:53.790 --> 00:45:57.250
are completely different from the ones that
they grew up with.

00:45:57.250 --> 00:46:02.480
And some of these things are popping up in
highly prestigious places as pilot programs.

00:46:02.480 --> 00:46:11.050
Harvard has one. UCSF has one. Students get
contact with patients early. They see the

00:46:11.050 --> 00:46:16.490
same small set of patients for a whole year,
so that they actually get to understand what

00:46:16.490 --> 00:46:22.490
it means to be sick in the context of living
an often complex and difficult life.

00:46:22.490 --> 00:46:27.140
They have lots and lots of interaction with
