00:46:30.890 --> 00:46:36.900
it wrong. The students in these programs love
them. They're incredibly difficult to get

00:46:36.900 --> 00:46:37.900
into.

00:46:37.900 --> 00:46:42.420
Everybody wants to get into this program,
but they only accommodate 15 or 20 people.

00:46:42.420 --> 00:46:47.450
Now my hope is that what will happen over
time when the evidence comes in that the people

00:46:47.450 --> 00:46:53.310
who get trained in this way become better
lawyers, teachers, and so on is that it will

00:46:53.310 --> 00:46:58.630
transform the way in which medical and legal
education occur.

00:46:58.630 --> 00:47:04.630
That's a big step, but it's not enough because
if they then enter the structure of their

00:47:04.630 --> 00:47:10.260
profession and all of the incentives that
are presently in place continue to be in place,

00:47:10.260 --> 00:47:15.710
this seems to me almost certain, It's almost
certainly gonna happen that all of the good

00:47:15.710 --> 00:47:23.760
stuff that they've learned gets destroyed,
or at least tackled, challenged.

00:47:23.760 --> 00:47:30.030
So, I hope you don't need the systems to collapse
completely so that you can build new ones

00:47:30.030 --> 00:47:36.700
on the ruins. I'm hoping that it's possible
to build new systems on, not quite ruins,

00:47:36.700 --> 00:47:42.260
but clearly defective existing ones. But I
don't know. I just don't know. There's an

00:47:42.260 --> 00:47:43.980
ideological component to this.

00:47:43.980 --> 00:47:49.151
Everyone thinks that the way to get what you
want is to make it worth people's while. That's

00:47:49.151 --> 00:47:55.910
wrong. Doctors want when people enter medical
school wanting to be doctors for the right

00:47:55.910 --> 00:48:01.051
reason. Everyone? No. Almost everyone? Yes.
You don't need to make it worth their while.

00:48:01.051 --> 00:48:06.200
You need to get out of their damn way so they
can do it the right way for the right reason

00:48:06.200 --> 00:48:10.630
on their own. And as long as we're wedded
to this ideology that comes from economics

00:48:10.630 --> 00:48:15.650
that nobody ever does anything except for
some self-interested outcome, we'll never

00:48:15.650 --> 00:48:18.010
redesign systems in the way that we need to.

00:48:18.010 --> 00:48:23.660
So, optimistic I'm not. But I'm also not hopeless.

00:48:23.660 --> 00:48:33.810
