We haven't really done the kind of careful

00:48:40.840 --> 00:48:48.300
and systematic inquiry. What we have done
is look at examples, books and articles, written

00:48:48.300 --> 00:48:53.140
about the guide of the actual practice of
teaching in medicine or the way in which teachers

00:48:53.140 --> 00:48:59.800
and doctors are trained and use these examples
to illustrate, we think often vividly, what's

00:48:59.800 --> 00:49:03.090
the wrong way and what's the right way to
engage in these practices.

00:49:03.090 --> 00:49:09.580
But we haven't done anything remotely like
counting. The sense I get is that the problem

00:49:09.580 --> 00:49:16.250
is less acute in Europe than it is the United
States, partly because one principle driver

00:49:16.250 --> 00:49:23.460
of all this obsession with rules is the threat
of being sued. And that's less of an issue.

00:49:23.460 --> 00:49:30.320
The culture of litigiousness that is characteristic
of the United States is close to unique to

00:49:30.320 --> 00:49:37.690
the United States. So there's a little bit
more room in Europe for people to spread their

00:49:37.690 --> 00:49:42.040
wings and take a chance without worrying that
the world will come crashing down around them.

00:49:42.040 --> 00:49:47.100
But I think the ideology that you have to
make it worth people's while to get them to

00:49:47.100 --> 00:49:53.750
do anything is pretty much as pervasive there
as it is in the US. And that's a major obstacle

00:49:53.750 --> 00:49:57.390
that needs to be overcome.

