that?

00:54:33.890 --> 00:54:39.230
&gt;&gt;Barry Schwartz: This is why there's nothing
in life that requires more wisdom than being

00:54:39.230 --> 00:54:45.440
a parent. It is terrible to use rewards to
get your kid toilet trained, unless you're

00:54:45.440 --> 00:54:48.290
desperate and nothing else works.

00:54:48.290 --> 00:54:53.790
It's terrible to use rewards to get kids to
do their homework, unless you're desperate

00:54:53.790 --> 00:54:59.940
and nothing else works. A lot of the seemingly,
from my point of view, foolish efforts to

00:54:59.940 --> 00:55:05.130
incentivize school performance that school
systems are now using, this is not the first

00:55:05.130 --> 00:55:06.200
thing they rush to.

00:55:06.200 --> 00:55:10.460
They rush to it basically in desperation.
If there was some other way to do it, they

00:55:10.460 --> 00:55:14.500
couldn't figure out what that was or they
didn't have the resources. So, they're gonna

00:55:14.500 --> 00:55:20.220
try to improve the quality of what the amount
that kids learn any damn way they can.

00:55:20.220 --> 00:55:24.370
And I think sometimes parents are desperate
enough that they do what they know in some

00:55:24.370 --> 00:55:29.270
sense is the wrong thing, because the goal
is important enough that you just have to

00:55:29.270 --> 00:55:34.510
get it. And then you'll worry about the negative
consequences of getting it in the wrong way

00:55:34.510 --> 00:55:36.610
further down the road.

00:55:36.610 --> 00:55:43.940
So again, I don't know, you shouldn't. Some
rewards are worse than others. Chocolate chips

00:55:43.940 --> 00:55:49.940
are worse than praise, for example. There
is some reason to think that recognition is

00:55:49.940 --> 00:56:00.520
a less tainting reward than material rewards
are. But even recognition is problematic because

00:56:00.520 --> 00:56:05.100
